# Zenith CMS Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Zenith is a monorepo managed with pnpm workspaces.
- Core logic is in `packages/core`.
- Frontend Admin is in `packages/admin`.
- Configuration is declarative via `cms.config.ts` in the root.

## Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript for everything.
- Prefer Zod for validation.
- All database models must inherit from `z_` internal collections prefix if system-related.
- Use `logger.info/error` instead of `console.log`.

## Directory Structure
- `packages/core/src/api`: API route factories.
- `packages/core/src/services`: Business logic services.
- `packages/core/src/database`: Mongoose models and connections.
- `packages/admin/src/pages`: Admin UI views.
